FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe group's latest quarterly economic
OL,8,Fprojections pointed to an increasingly
OL,9,Fgloomy outlook as the war between US-
OL,10,FIsraeli and Iranian forces weighs on
OL,11,Feconomies globally, with the UK set
OL,12,Ffor slower growth and rising inflation.
OL,14,FIt indicated that the Bank of
OL,15,FEngland's committee rate-setters are
OL,16,Flikely to increase interest rates this
OL,17,Fsummer as a result, with the potential
OL,18,Ffor up to six more hikes in a more
OL,19,Fsevere scenario.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FOn Thursday, the Bank's Monetary
OL,8,FPolicy Committee will vote on whether
OL,9,Fto keep interest rates at their
OL,10,Fcurrent level of 3.75%.
OL,12,FNiesr said it expects interest rates
OL,13,Fto be held at this meeting, but
OL,14,Fpredicted they will be increased to 4%
OL,15,Fin July ` staying at this level
OL,16,Fthrough the rest of the year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FHowever, it said a severe scenario,
OL,8,Fwhich would see further inflationary
OL,9,Fpressure from a continuing conflict,
OL,10,Fcould result in rates rising as high
OL,11,Fas 5.25%.
OL,13,FIn its best-case scenario which would
OL,14,Finclude a resolution in the Middle
OL,15,FEast this year, the organisation still
OL,16,Fpointed towards a slowdown in economic
OL,17,Fgrowth to 0.9% for 2026, compared with
OL,18,F1.4% growth in 2025.
OL,20,FThe group said growth is likely to
OL,21,Fimprove marginally to 1% in 2027.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FIn its previous outlook, Niesr had
OL,8,Fpredicted 1.4% growth this year and
OL,9,F1.3% growth in 2027.
OL,11,FEven with a swift resolution to the
OL,12,Fconflict, Niesr said the UK economy
OL,13,Fwill be around #35 billion smaller in
OL,14,F2026 and 2027, casting uncertainty
OL,15,Fover the Chancellor's ambitions to
OL,16,Fgrow the UK economy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FHowever, Niesr's deputy director for
OL,8,Fmacroeconomics Stephen Millard said an
OL,9,Fadverse situation is likely to knock
OL,10,Faround 0.4 percentage points off
OL,11,Fgrowth over the next two years.
OL,13,FThe forecasts also indicated that
OL,14,Finflation, which lifted to 3.3% last
OL,15,Fmonth, will slow to 2.5%.
OL,17,FBut it is then expected to shoot
OL,18,Fhigher as higher energy prices drive
OL,19,Ffurther inflation, with it expected to
OL,20,Fpeak at 4.1% in January next year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FNiesr said it expects inflation will
OL,8,Fnot drop back to the Bank of England's
OL,9,F2% target rate until 2028 as a result.
OL,11,FInflation is set to surpass wage
OL,12,Fgrowth, which is predicted to slow to
OL,13,F3.3% next year, putting pressure of
OL,14,Fhousehold finances.
OL,16,FGrowth in real personal disposable
OL,17,Fincome is forecast to slow to 1% in
OL,18,F2026 and 0.6% in 2027, with low-income
OL,19,Fhouseholds who spend a higher
OL,20,Fproportion of their income on energy
OL,21,Fbeing hit the hardest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1777489866
OL,3,CUK economy set for #35bn hit from
OL,4,CMiddle East energy crisis, think tank
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FDavid Aikman, Niesr director, said:
OL,8,F"This is a serious blow to the
OL,9,FGovernment's mission to get the UK
OL,10,Feconomy growing again.
OL,12,F"The Middle East conflict has laid
OL,13,Fbare the fact that the UK remains
OL,14,Fhighly exposed to global energy shocks.
OL,16,F"Even if hostilities ease rapidly,
OL,17,Fhigher energy prices will leave
OL,18,Fhouseholds poorer, businesses facing
OL,19,Fhigher costs, and the economy
OL,20,Fmaterially smaller than we expected
OL,21,Fonly a few months ago."
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU}D@WO]
